##Under the epidemic, ordinary people who put up with it and kept going

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

As a member of Jiangxi Medical Team for Hubei Province, the first close contact between "Tian Luo" and the new coronary pneumonia patient is an urgent and dangerous rescue.

It was at the intensive-care unit in Wuhan, where a patient's Oxygenation dropped precipitously, causing difficulty breathing, sweating profusely, and the screeching of the detector sounded like the countdown to death, a race for life and death has begun. At this point, the only option is to create an artificial airway for the patient immediately. "snail" wearing a protective mask rushed up to protect the lips, insert laryngoscope, laryngoscope, insert tracheal catheter. After a series of deft maneuvers, the intubation was completed, and the patient's life was saved as the screen Oxygenation up.

At this time, "Tian Luo" just suddenly felt scared, heart, liver, spleen and lung all seized together. TRACHEAL INTUBATION is the most dangerous part of rescuing a newly crowned patient because the doctor has to be close to the patient's Open Airways, which constantly spew the virus. "I won't win, will I? " The thought lingered for at least ten minutes in the mind of the non-communicable Disease Professional.

01

"Tian Snail" , a doctor from Jiangxi medical team supporting Hubei Province
“
Wuhan, HERE WE COME!

Put the time back to the second day of the Lunar New Year, originally intended in the fourth day and long-distance love girlfriend in Hangzhou to meet the "Tian Luo" temporary notice, became a member of the medical team of Jiangxi Aid Hubei. He didn't have time to placate his family, and the next day he headed straight to Wuhan. Although he had been looking forward to the fourth grade meeting, it was a rare time of year for the long distance couple to get together.

When "Tian Snail" and 137 other medical personnel landed in Wuhan the first moment, they felt the grim atmosphere of the epidemic front. The Tianhe Terminal, China's No. Fourteen airport with nearly 40,000 passengers, had no passengers except for them and the ground crew. The Director of Wuhan's Fifth Hospital, who had come to meet the team, bowed deeply to each of the three buses.

"I could see he was about to cry. "

It was not clear at the time why the Dean was so excited. It wasn't until, after a day of personal training and brief exchanges on epidemic prevention, and with some trepidation, that he formally took over the ICU wards of the intensive-care unit in Wuhan, that he realized that the workload of the doctors of the five hospitals had reached six to nine times that of a normal day, the remaining five doctors, including the 56-year-old chief, are on the verge of overshooting. The patients lying in the ward look different, calm, pain, panic... "Tian Luo" know, when a common, fragile, powerless life to face the fate of the unknown, any language is extremely Pale. He's here to save lives, save patients'lives, save hospitals.

The arrival of the Jiangxi Hubei Team brought a ray of hope to the doctors of the five hospitals in Wuhan, and even the patients seemed to see a turning point. When the "snail" first enters the intensive-care unit, an uncle, who is hooked up to a breathing machine and too sick to speak, gives him a difficult thumbs-up.

Patients in critical condition, I heard that is the aid team came, difficult to "snail" thumbs up
At the same time, aid is slowly being put in place, including a large number of medical supplies donated by members of the Celai car club. "Tian Luo" in the "Weilai community" release of the "note to Hubei Province" let him inadvertently become the docking car friends and the hospital liaison, for the national linkage added a user chain with a glimmer. As Mr. Lu Xun said: "A minute of heat, a minute of light. So that the firefly general, but also in the dark can be a little light, do not have to wait for the torch. "

Today is the 25th day of Tianluo's first-line battle as a member of the Hubei medical team. In the 25th day, he experienced a transformation from panic to calm and resolute, from uneasy anxiety to calm and resolute. He wrote in "Yuan e notes" : "Now like a very brave soldier, every time out, must be triumphant return. "

"Tian Snail" and his comrades successfully rescued the first patient transferred out of the Intensive Care Unit
According to the old director's suggestion, "Tian Luo" will wear diapers when working. However, this does not mean that everything is fine, at first because of the feeling of embarrassment, how he could not pee, until the moment really can not hold back, the heart has a kind of indescribable taste.

There was danger and warmth on the battlefield. In the first few days, in addition to the psychological pressure to face, "Tianluo" also face from the lifestyle and regional differences. After the local hospital learned that they are not used to Wuhan's diet, specially prepared chili sauce, hoping to help them find the taste of home. In addition, Wuhan Dialect, the initial communication with the patient can only even guess, but slowly get used to, "Tian Snail" and patients, local doctors have gradually formed a tacit understanding. When the shift change, shift change, said: "I am hungry and tired. " , the successor will be followed by a sentence: "also urgent urine" , we have a tacit understanding to laugh.

Every day after work to take off the spacesuit-like protective equipment, never feel oxygen is so fresh "field snail" , will see the scenery in the street, the changes he felt in the hospital updated to the "notes to the Hubei Province. He would linger for a moment on his way back to his post, past the corner of Hanyang Avenue. It was a calm in the eye of the storm. In a quarter of an hour, only three cars, five bicycles and six pedestrians passed by. The security guard at the gate told him that the street used to be very busy. His post gives us a real sense of the oppression, tension and hope on the front lines of the fight against the pandemic.

The old hustle and bustle of Hanyang Boulevard is now covered with viruses
In a few days ago, "yuan e notes" , "Tian Luo" recorded a special experience. After eating two packets of instant noodles in a row, he suddenly felt toothache. At this juncture, in order to cooperate with the epidemic prevention work, all the stomatological clinics in Wuhan were closed. At first, he could endure it, but as the saying goes, "toothache is not a disease. It hurts like hell. " In his most desperate moment, Wuhan No. 1 stomatological hospital contacted him and opened a green channel for him.

In addition to the concern from the comrades-in-arms, active users of more than 30,000 to the "Weilai community" , "Tianluo" every day also received a lot of concern and encouragement.

"Come back safe. "
"seeing your updates makes me feel more secure. Protect yourself so you can help others! "
"when the outbreak is over, please send a picture of your triumphant return and refuel. Send me an address and I'll send you a box of mutton. "

This makes the "field snail" in a foreign land feel friendly and warm, and draw strength from it, and continue to move forward.

02

Gao Yan, a volunteer of psychological assistance in the outbreak
“
An inaudible but crushing cry

In the process of fighting in the front, "snail" found that the virus is naturally the current enemy, and the psychological problems caused by the epidemic, is another invisible enemy.

On the day that the five hospitals became designated hospitals for the epidemic, the emergency department directors, who had been working hard for five days and five nights in a row, "roared" in a crying voice in the face of the nearly paralyzed emergency department, which had surged to more than one thousand, four hundred patients, "Don't we want to live, don't we want to go home for the New Year? "

One patient, distraught after waiting in line for more than four hours, threw a fistful of cash down the hall and sat on the floor. "What do you need money for? "

"Tian Luo" also has to face the family worried about its "blame" , because of pressure-induced pulpitis, and tried their best but failed to recover from the hands of death of a patient's frustration. "Yuan e notes" is his cohesive "fire source" , "Weilai community" has become the narrative "tree hole" , will see, hear, think, said and strangers friends.

Gao Yan, who is also a user of Weilai and a psychological service practitioner, felt the psychological assistance gap in the whirlpool of the epidemic. Gao Yan, a native of Wuhan, saw a fellow doctor struggle in the front line of the epidemic for more than half a month. Every day before he went to work, he had to do a long psychological struggle in the parking lot, then in the group of Students said a "comrades, I have to go up again, " and then walked into the ward, after work to call peace, "I'm OK, today is OK! ". Another classmate also sent a request for help, his colleagues are suspected patients, low fever, children and small, her husband has not rushed back to Wuhan, as long as the news related to the epidemic, anxious to tears.

Mental health is as important as physical health in an outbreak, and both are protective shields against the virus. Gao Wenbin, a researcher at the Institute of Psychology at the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said: "In some patients, the severity or instability of symptoms has a lot to do with their emotional state. "

On the day of the closure, Gao Yan immediately set about contacting a psychological consultant to form a group of volunteers for psychological care. At the same time, she also made use of the international resources in the "Weilai community" to gather her friends. Despite the difficulties, the procurement of anti-epidemic materials from overseas did not stop for a moment, weilai companies in the United States and Germany are also involved in the procurement and trans-shipment process of materials. "The support and warmth of my counselors and the spontaneous solidarity of so many strangers to help the affected areas are all positive inspirations for me, " Gao said

Gather the strength of Weilai Wuhan Automobile Association to Donate Materials for Wuhan Hospital
On January 24, Gao Yan's group of volunteers for psychological care officially launched, "psychological support can provide companionship, listening, knowledge, and some stabilization techniques, " she says. By listening and warm empathy, we enable the person to relieve anxiety, maintain emotional stability, and provide information support."The service process was developed at the beginning of the team, working Mechanism. Important Peer Support, supervisory support, and effective contingency mechanisms are also available within the group.

Gao Yan and the team provide help to those who seek psychological counseling
The road of psychological care is not smooth, trivial problems gradually come. For example, the first-line medical staff to work mostly near midnight, and this time domestic consultants may have been resting. Gao Yan participated in the "heart to fight the epidemic" volunteer team, together with "ACHPPI members" (international association of Chinese psychological and Aid Professional Association) volunteer team mobilized Chinese psychological aid volunteers in the United States, Canada and other places to take advantage of jet lag, a round-the-clock psychological assistance service was provided. A volunteer who graduated from the Wuhan University provided a free hotline program he developed to solve the technical problems of communication between help seekers and overseas consultants.

In addition, many medical staff tried their best to stay in the ward for more than 10 hours in order to reduce the use of protective clothing, so Gao Yan's team added self-help guidance with pictures and words, and a "word tree hole" for sharing, followed by a week of nightly psych audio. Convenient medical personnel at any time through Wechat, psychological assistance telephone channels to obtain a certain degree of comfort and encouragement.

As the epidemic dragged on, more and more people sought psychological care and assistance:

A nurse's colleagues, a family of four, two people were admitted to isolation ward, leaving the husband and two-year-old children. Now, the husband is also showing symptoms of cough and fever. "What should I do with the doll? " The nurse could not stop crying.
A medical staff pregnant soon, her husband and mother-in-law have returned home, she stayed in Wuhan Line work. After the night shift, I had this weird stomach ache. Hard to go down the stairs, but has been unable to get a car to the hospital, could not help crying.

At peak times, you can get more than four requests a day, filled with the anxiety, sadness, anger, confusion, and crying of the person asking for help. Many volunteers work at least four hours a day, and "triage" assistants have seen thousands of people.

"after completing the docking at two or three in the morning, she had to get up before eight to continue her work. " Although her biological clock was completely disrupted, Gao Yan remained calm and aware of the pressures and emotions of being in the midst of an epidemic call for help, "It's clear to me that this is a stressful situation, and I use some psychological relaxation or mindfulness to help me cope. Since you can't sleep, do what you can to keep your information channels open and focus on positive resources, which can help people around you even a little bit and increase your sense of worth, mobilize the resources around, "my family, especially the children's innocent smile, is my epidemic in the warmth and support! "

When talking about the volunteer work of psychological care, Gao said, "volunteers for psychological care are like dew, a small drop that moistens those who are not yet illuminated by the sun in the dark night. When the sun shines, the dew disappears. The haze of hope reality does not cover the sunshine in everyone's heart. "

03

“
Shine, even if it's faint

Milan Kundera said, "for immortality, there is a small immortality and a big immortality. A small immortality is a person who leaves a memory in the mind of someone who knows him; a big immortality is a person who leaves a memory in the mind of someone who does not know him. "

Immortality always radiates, constantly resonating. "Weilai community" has quietly become an epidemic of light-emitting cohesion platform. "Tianluo" in the "notes to Hubei Aid, " said, "not only to buy a car" , "like a warm home. In contrast to the full-open environment that brings unpredictable social pressures, the "Weilai community" pool of users with the same pulse, under the weight of the epidemic, to stimulate a new emotional chain of power.

More and more Weilai users are taking action to solidify and strengthen this brand new emotional connection. Human Nature has its own weakness, but also has its own strong. Some people through the "Weilai community" "report peace" , tell friends the real situation of the front line; others through the community temporarily from High Pressure; More people like "Tian Luo" doctor and psychological assistance volunteers like Gao Yan, to join the seemingly ordinary but emitting a glimmer of action to.

In the "Weilai community" , there are a lot of Endlessly "anti-epidemic" action, although only a few words.

There's a warm. Weilai user, who is called the host Of@asakusa Temple, said, although we can not go to the first-line hospital, nor can we go backward to save the lives of infected people, but we can go to the blood donation house and donate blood, and we can use every bit of love to create a mighty force to fight against coronavirus.

Persevering. Weilai USER@ZHAOJING, on duty at the railway station temperature measurement, stick to the post, strictly check the dead guard. A user named@BN -chocolate Hj said wittily, "as a new community worker, I come to work at 8 am every day. ".

There's no one to help. Wei Lai User@zhang Kai 2701 was on duty at the expressway when a truck full of 10 tons of raw pork suddenly broke down. Together with another User@fang Daoping, they drove the truck out of the expressway by force.

There's something warm about it. Weilai user@comiclink bought 10,000 Jin of vegetables, drove his ES8 towed flatbed truck to donate to the community.

On the "Weilai community" , everyone sees life itself under the epidemic, and every Weilai user glimmers.

Sometimes, Ulai users bring their families together. When a pregnant woman asked Gao Yan for help, her baby was just over a year old and her husband was admitted to the hospital. "there is no milk powder at home, and the Internet is also out of luck, " cried the supplicant. Gao offered psychological care to the supplicant over the phone, while asking her husband to buy milk powder and deliver it to the supplicant's home. Gao's husband wore a two-layer disposable raincoat as a protective suit, a pair of diving glasses as goggles, a three-layer head covering and a two-layer mask, and left the house. In the outbreak, the "Weilai community" quickly connected one after another of the glimmer, flashing in those who are familiar with or unfamiliar with the need to help people.

"I just don't feel like I have enough time. I go to bed at two or three in a couple of days, and I can get up before eight in the morning. " Facing the overwhelming amount of information and the negative emotions of the rescuers, Gao Yan, who is at the center of the Whirlpool, is under tremendous pressure. Psychological help "sometimes it's healing, often it's helping, always it's comforting, " and after a little self-care and respite, she continues to feel like she could talk to me, if you like. "To help them in my way, the harder it is, the stronger it is, because I believe that no winter is insurmountable, no midsummer will not come. ".

"Tianluo" wrote happily and proudly in "notes for Hubei" , "Our results were clear, and when I returned to the ER as a volunteer, the sight was enough to soothe us these days. The Madness was gone. The crowded emergency room, half a month before, was quiet again. The infusion rooms were empty of the sad faces of the day. I think this is what we have achieved and it will be the glory of our lives."

"To me, it doesn't matter if you're a hero or not. It's only true if you can help them, " he said, when many people praised him and thought he was a hero

Gao Wenbin, a researcher at the Institute of Psychology at the Chinese Academy of Sciences, said: "In some patients, the severity or instability of symptoms has a lot to do with their emotional state. "

On the day of the closure, Gao Yan immediately set about contacting a psychological consultant to form a group of volunteers for psychological care. At the same time, she also made use of the international resources in the "Weilai community" to gather her friends. Despite the difficulties, the procurement of anti-epidemic materials from overseas did not stop for a moment, weilai companies in the United States and Germany are also involved in the procurement and trans-shipment process of materials. "The support and warmth of my counselors and the spontaneous solidarity of so many strangers to help the affected areas are all positive inspirations for me, " Gao said

In the process of fighting in the front, "snail" found that the virus is naturally the current enemy, and the psychological problems caused by the epidemic, is another invisible enemy.

On the day that the five hospitals became designated hospitals for the epidemic, the emergency department directors, who had been working hard for five days and five nights in a row, "roared" in a crying voice in the face of the nearly paralyzed emergency department, which had surged to more than one thousand, four hundred patients, "Don't we want to live, don't we want to go home for the New Year? "

One patient, distraught after waiting in line for more than four hours, threw a fistful of cash down the hall and sat on the floor. "What do you need money for? "

"Tian Luo" also has to face the family worried about its "blame" , because of pressure-induced pulpitis, and tried their best but failed to recover from the hands of death of a patient's frustration. "Yuan e notes" is his cohesive "fire source" , "Weilai community" has become the narrative "tree hole" , will see, hear, think, said and strangers friends.

Gao Yan, who is also a user of Weilai and a psychological service practitioner, felt the psychological assistance gap in the whirlpool of the epidemic. Gao Yan, a native of Wuhan, saw a fellow doctor struggle in the front line of the epidemic for more than half a month. Every day before he went to work, he had to do a long psychological struggle in the parking lot, then in the group of Students said a "comrades, I have to go up again, " and then walked into the ward, after work to call peace, "I'm OK, today is OK! ". Another classmate also sent a request for help, his colleagues are suspected patients, low fever, children and small, her husband has not rushed back to Wuhan, as long as the news related to the epidemic, anxious to tears.

Gather the strength of Weilai Wuhan Automobile Association to Donate Materials for Wuhan Hospital

On January 24, Gao Yan's group of volunteers for psychological care officially launched, "psychological support can provide companionship, listening, knowledge, and some stabilization techniques, " she says. By listening and warm empathy, we enable the person to relieve anxiety, maintain emotional stability, and provide information support."The service process was developed at the beginning of the team, working Mechanism. Important Peer Support, supervisory support, and effective contingency mechanisms are also available within the group.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Gao Yan and the team provide help to those who seek psychological counseling

The road of psychological care is not smooth, trivial problems gradually come. For example, the first-line medical staff to work mostly near midnight, and this time domestic consultants may have been resting. Gao Yan participated in the "heart to fight the epidemic" volunteer team, together with "ACHPPI members" (international association of Chinese psychological and Aid Professional Association) volunteer team mobilized Chinese psychological aid volunteers in the United States, Canada and other places to take advantage of jet lag, a round-the-clock psychological assistance service was provided. A volunteer who graduated from the Wuhan University provided a free hotline program he developed to solve the technical problems of communication between help seekers and overseas consultants.

In addition, many medical staff tried their best to stay in the ward for more than 10 hours in order to reduce the use of protective clothing, so Gao Yan's team added self-help guidance with pictures and words, and a "word tree hole" for sharing, followed by a week of nightly psych audio. Convenient medical personnel at any time through Wechat, psychological assistance telephone channels to obtain a certain degree of comfort and encouragement.

As the epidemic dragged on, more and more people sought psychological care and assistance:

A nurse's colleagues, a family of four, two people were admitted to isolation ward, leaving the husband and two-year-old children. Now, the husband is also showing symptoms of cough and fever. "What should I do with the doll? " The nurse could not stop crying.
A medical staff pregnant soon, her husband and mother-in-law have returned home, she stayed in Wuhan Line work. After the night shift, I had this weird stomach ache. Hard to go down the stairs, but has been unable to get a car to the hospital, could not help crying.

At peak times, you can get more than four requests a day, filled with the anxiety, sadness, anger, confusion, and crying of the person asking for help. Many volunteers work at least four hours a day, and "triage" assistants have seen thousands of people.

"after completing the docking at two or three in the morning, she had to get up before eight to continue her work. " Although her biological clock was completely disrupted, Gao Yan remained calm and aware of the pressures and emotions of being in the midst of an epidemic call for help, "It's clear to me that this is a stressful situation, and I use some psychological relaxation or mindfulness to help me cope. Since you can't sleep, do what you can to keep your information channels open and focus on positive resources, which can help people around you even a little bit and increase your sense of worth, mobilize the resources around, "my family, especially the children's innocent smile, is my epidemic in the warmth and support! "

When talking about the volunteer work of psychological care, Gao said, "volunteers for psychological care are like dew, a small drop that moistens those who are not yet illuminated by the sun in the dark night. When the sun shines, the dew disappears. The haze of hope reality does not cover the sunshine in everyone's heart. "

Shine, even if it's faint

Milan Kundera said, "for immortality, there is a small immortality and a big immortality. A small immortality is a person who leaves a memory in the mind of someone who knows him; a big immortality is a person who leaves a memory in the mind of someone who does not know him. "

Immortality always radiates, constantly resonating. "Weilai community" has quietly become an epidemic of light-emitting cohesion platform. "Tianluo" in the "notes to Hubei Aid, " said, "not only to buy a car" , "like a warm home. In contrast to the full-open environment that brings unpredictable social pressures, the "Weilai community" pool of users with the same pulse, under the weight of the epidemic, to stimulate a new emotional chain of power.

More and more Weilai users are taking action to solidify and strengthen this brand new emotional connection. Human Nature has its own weakness, but also has its own strong. Some people through the "Weilai community" "report peace" , tell friends the real situation of the front line; others through the community temporarily from High Pressure; More people like "Tian Luo" doctor and psychological assistance volunteers like Gao Yan, to join the seemingly ordinary but emitting a glimmer of action to.

In the "Weilai community" , there are a lot of Endlessly "anti-epidemic" action, although only a few words.

Weilai user, who is called the host Of@asakusa Temple, said, although we can not go to the first-line hospital, nor can we go backward to save the lives of infected people, but we can go to the blood donation house and donate blood, and we can use every bit of love to create a mighty force to fight against coronavirus.

Persevering. Weilai USER@ZHAOJING, on duty at the railway station temperature measurement, stick to the post, strictly check the dead guard. A user named@BN -chocolate Hj said wittily, "as a new community worker, I come to work at 8 am every day. ".

There's no one to help. Wei Lai User@zhang Kai 2701 was on duty at the expressway when a truck full of 10 tons of raw pork suddenly broke down. Together with another User@fang Daoping, they drove the truck out of the expressway by force.

There's something warm about it. Weilai user@comiclink bought 10,000 Jin of vegetables, drove his ES8 towed flatbed truck to donate to the community.

On the "Weilai community" , everyone sees life itself under the epidemic, and every Weilai user glimmers.

Sometimes, Ulai users bring their families together. When a pregnant woman asked Gao Yan for help, her baby was just over a year old and her husband was admitted to the hospital. "there is no milk powder at home, and the Internet is also out of luck, " cried the supplicant. Gao offered psychological care to the supplicant over the phone, while asking her husband to buy milk powder and deliver it to the supplicant's home. Gao's husband wore a two-layer disposable raincoat as a protective suit, a pair of diving glasses as goggles, a three-layer head covering and a two-layer mask, and left the house. In the outbreak, the "Weilai community" quickly connected one after another of the glimmer, flashing in those who are familiar with or unfamiliar with the need to help people.

"I just don't feel like I have enough time. I go to bed at two or three in a couple of days, and I can get up before eight in the morning. " Facing the overwhelming amount of information and the negative emotions of the rescuers, Gao Yan, who is at the center of the Whirlpool, is under tremendous pressure. Psychological help "sometimes it's healing, often it's helping, always it's comforting, " and after a little self-care and respite, she continues to feel like she could talk to me, if you like. "To help them in my way, the harder it is, the stronger it is, because I believe that no winter is insurmountable, no midsummer will not come. ".

"Tianluo" wrote happily and proudly in "notes for Hubei" , "Our results were clear, and when I returned to the ER as a volunteer, the sight was enough to soothe us these days. The Madness was gone. The crowded emergency room, half a month before, was quiet again. The infusion rooms were empty of the sad faces of the day. I think this is what we have achieved and it will be the glory of our lives."

"To me, it doesn't matter if you're a hero or not. It's only true if you can help them, " he said, when many people praised him and thought he was a hero
